001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.util;
002
003/**
004 * Represents a function that accepts three input arguments and produces a result.
005 *
006 * <p>This functional interface is similar to {@link java.util.function.BiFunction},
007 * but it supports three parameters instead of two. It is useful in scenarios
008 * where a computation or transformation requires three inputs to generate an output.
009 *
010 * <p>The first argument, {@code T}, represents the primary input or entity being processed.
011 * The second argument, {@code U}, provides supporting data or configuration.
012 * The third argument, {@code V}, offers additional context necessary for computation.
013 * The function then produces a result of type {@code R}.
014 *
015 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate ğŸ’ğŸ‘¨ğŸ’»
016 */
017@FunctionalInterface
018public interface TriFunction<T, U, V, R> {
019
020   /**
021    * Applies this function to the given arguments and returns a result.
022    *
023    * @param t The first input argument.
024    * @param u The second input argument.
025    * @param v The third input argument.
026    * @return The computed result of type {@code R}.
027    */
028   R apply(T t, U u, V v);
029}
